data.title: Gosling named head coach of Dinos women’s hockey program
data.meta_description: CALGARY – Josh Gosling has been named the head coach of the University of Calgary Dinos Women's Hockey Joan Snyder Program of Excellence, Dinos Director of Athletics
data.text:
Jayden Images - Chris Lindsey

Women's Hockey 5/29/2024 1:00:00 PM Dinos Communications

Gosling named head coach of Dinos women’s hockey program

CALGARY – Josh Gosling has been named the head coach of the University of Calgary Dinos Women's Hockey Joan Snyder Program of Excellence, Dinos Director of Athletics Ben Matchett announced Wednesday.

Gosling, who was elevated to interim head coach of the program this past fall, spent two seasons as associate head coach, working alongside Carla MacLeod. He officially becomes the seventh head coach in Dinos women's hockey history.

"Josh stepped into the head coach role mid-season last year and did an admirable job," Matchett said. "His collaborative approach, along with his demonstrated ability to recruit and build strong relationships with his athletes, are among the ingredients that will make him successful in this role. We're excited for what's next in the Joan Snyder Program of Excellence."

Following the departure of MacLeod to the Professional Women's Hockey League, Gosling compiled a record of 10-10-2 as interim head coach. The Dinos won nine of their final 14 regular season games to secure the fifth seed in the Canada West Playoffs. Under Gosling's guidance, Calgary defeated the Saskatchewan Huskies on the road in the conference quarterfinal, overcoming a Game 1 loss, to clinch their first postseason series victory since 2015.

"I am grateful for the opportunity to lead the Dinos women's hockey program and confident in the direction this team is heading," Gosling said. "I am excited to work with everyone involved and represent the prestigious University of Calgary."

Gosling joined the Dinos in August of 2021 from Edge School, a private school for Grades 4-12 located just west of Calgary, where he served as the head coach of their boy's U17 prep team.

Gosling also brings experience from various levels with Hockey Alberta and is a Hockey Canada Certified Skills Coach.

The Joan Snyder Program of Excellence in Women's Hockey has supported the Dinos women's hockey team since 2011, enhancing coaching excellence, elite competition and sport services, and providing scholarships to student-athletes.
